sentences: Mana Mikura (三倉 茉奈, Mikura Mana) and Kana Mikura (三倉 佳奈, Mikura Kana) (born February 23, 1986) are Japanese identical twin sister actresses.
Mana is the older one, born 7 minutes before Kana.
In 1996, they appeared in the Asadora Futarikko, playing the main twin characters as children.
In March 2008, both graduated from Kwansei Gakuin University.
In 2008, they starred in the Asadora Dandan about twins separated in infancy.
